sba","marks":1,"options":["Creola bodies = whorls of shed epithelium; Charcot-Leyden crystals = crystals within aggregate of eosinophils; Curschmann\u0027s spirals = mucus casts containing inflammatory cells","Creola bodies = whorls of shed epithelium; Charcot-Leyden crystals = mucus casts containing inflammatory cells; Curschmann\u0027s spirals = crystals within aggregate of eosinophils","Creola bodies = crystals within aggregate of eosinophils; Charcot-Leyden crystals = mucus casts containing inflammatory cells; Curschmann\u0027s spirals = whorls of shed epithelium","Creola bodies = mucus casts containing inflammatory cells; Charcot-Leyden crystals = crystals within aggregate of eosinophils; Curschmann\u0027s spirals = whorls of shed epithelium","Creola bodies = crystals within aggregate of eosinophils; Charcot-Leyden crystals = whorls of shed epithelium; Curschmann\u0027s spirals = mucus casts containing inflammatory cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreola bodies\u003C/strong\u003E are whorls of shed epithelium found in the sputum of asthma patients. \u003Cstrong\u003ECharcot-Leyden crystals\u003C/strong\u003E are formed from the breakdown of eosinophils and are found in the sputum of asthma patients. \u003Cstrong\u003ECurschmann\u0027s spirals\u003C/strong\u003E are mucus casts containing inflammatory cells, often seen in asthma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Asthmatic sputum contains clusters of desquamated epithelial cells called Creola bodies.","Degradation of eosinophils in asthmatic airways produces characteristic Charcot-Leyden crystals.","Curschmann\u0027s spirals are twisted strands of mucus containing entrapped inflammatory cells seen in asthmatic sputum."],"references":["Mart\u00ednez-Rivera C, Crespo A, Pinedo-Sierra C, Garc\u00eda-Rivero JL, Pallar\u00e9s-Sanmart\u00edn A, Marina-Malanda N, Pascual-Erquicia S, Padilla A, Mayoralas-Alises S, Plaza V, L\u00f